1. He was worried about wasting time.
2. He was concerned about losing focus.
3. He was afraid of not being able to solve his problem due to distraction.
4. He was aware of the importance of concentration for solving his problem.
5. He recognized the negative impact of distraction on his productivity.
6. He knew that getting sidetracked would hinder his progress.
7. He understood that his problem required his undivided attention.